The Huawei Mate40 Pro is coming to South Africa and you can pre-order it now. This smartphone offers a breath-taking Space Ring design and premium performance to give you everything you could possibly want in a smartphone. Click here to buy the Huawei Mate40 Pro. If you long to upgrade to the latest in smartphone innovation, the Huawei Mate40 Pro is the best choice. The Mate40 Pro packs the best hardware to give you a truly elite user experience. This includes the world’s first 5nm 5G SoC, the Kirin 9000, to drive unprecedented performance and power efficiency. The Mate40 Pro boasts 8GB RAM and 256GB of storage to make sure your device is always running smoothly, and it supports Wi-Fi 6 and Bluetooth 5.2. The 4,400mAh battery is another great feature of the Mate40 Pro, as it supports SuperCharge in both wired and wireless forms. Wired SuperCharge supports up to 66W charging, while wireless SuperCharge supports up to 50W. Huawei has a reputation for elite smartphone cameras and the Mate40 Pro continues this trend. It boasts a triple-lens Leica camera system on the rear, which includes a 50MP primary lens. The Mate40 Pro also has a 12MP periscope telephoto lens and a 20MP ultrawide lens to make it easy to take different types of photos. On the front, a dual-lens camera system includes a 13MP ultrawide lens and a time-of-flight 3D lens to offer better depth perception and accurate biometric scanning. The camera also benefits from Huawei’s continuous innovation in the photography industry, and offers the following technologies: Full Pixel Octa PD AutoFocus.
Algorithms that enhance quality and distortion for photos taken with a wide field of view.
10x hybrid zoom and 50x digital zoom.
Image stabilisation.
Tracking Shot – which lets the user choose the main subject and have the camera follow them when either they or the camera move.
XD Fusion HDR video. The Mate40 Pro boasts a 6.76-inch, 2,772 x 1,344 OLED display which makes consuming content on the smartphone a pleasure. This display underscores the fantastic design of this device, which is inspired by the Mate30 Pro’s Halo ring design. Called Space Ring, this new design represents the fearless and unwavering attitude of exploring the new and unknown. The Mate40 Pro has a recommended price of R19,999. Pre-order the Huawei Mate40 Pro now, simply be one of the first 200 customers to pay R500 and receive an extra R1500 discount off on the balance of the purchase price. Together with this discount, the first 200 will also receive a complimentary bundle consisting of the new Huawei Freebuds 4i, the Huawei GT 2e watch, a Huawei Smart Scale and our HUAWEI VIP Service. Exclusive to the Huawei Store (Online) . T&C’s apply. Click here to buy the Huawei Mate40 Pro. <img class="size-full wp-image-478215 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Mate-40-pro-2.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Mate-40-pro-2.jpg 640w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Mate-40-pro-2-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="size-full wp-image-478217 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Mate-40-pro-3.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Mate-40-pro-3.jpg 640w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Mate-40-pro-3-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> This article was published in partnership with Huawei.